comments.body:
We spent some time working on this the other day just to understand the problem a bit. I think ideally, the formatter should be able to return multiple representations in different MIME types, e.g. `image/png` and `text/html`. I'm also curious as to whether  some portions of the implementation would be reusable enough that they should go into [Microsoft.DotNet.Interactive.Formatting](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Microsoft.DotNet.Interactive.Formatting/) so that similar extensions for other image libraries can make use of them.

Related: https://github.com/dotnet/interactive/issues/1374

@lytesfazion @cerasamson @AngleQian @colombod
